    public class OMPanelResults
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    Creates and shows the results panel for this software tool. Allows the user to inspect the simulation results and to view distribution charts.
    Author:
    A. Schoedon

      • createDistributionPanel

        public javax.swing.JPanel createDistributionPanel(java.lang.String title,
                                         org.apache.commons.math.stat.descriptive.DescriptiveStatistics statistics,
                                         OMRoomType roomType,
                                         boolean preview,
                                         boolean mouseEvent)
        Creates a panel displaying the distribution chart of certain selected statistical values.
        Parameters:
        title - The headline of the chart. Will be hidden if set to null.
        statistics - The selected statistics of a campaign containing all needed values.
        roomType - The room type to determine the color of the chart.
        preview - Will hide annotations, labels and headlines if set true.
        mouseEvent - Will enable mouseClickedEvent if set true. Use with care, and only inside the results panel. Set to false if you are unsure what you are doing.
        Returns:
        A chart displaying the distribution of certain selected statistical values.
